  "description": [
    "Friday 1 July 1960 Boat Owners Must Register Craft Rated Over 10 HP Navymen who own their own motorpowered boats either in board or outboard rated at more than 10 horsepower must have them registered and numbered under the Federal Boating Act of 1958 The Coast Guard will issue numbers to boats registered in the 15 states and the District of Columbia which have not yet adopted their own numbering systems There states are Alas ka Connecticut Georgia Hawaii Ida h o Maine Massachusetts low a Nevada N w Hampshire New Jersey Pennsylvania Ten nessee Wyoming and Washing ton Boat owners may obtain Fed eral Certificates of Number ap plication forms at any local post office The completed form and a 3 U 0 fee must be filed with the post office At that time a blue Federal Boating Stamp will be affixed to the application and a temporary certificate will be is sued This certificate will serve as proof of compliance with the law until the application has been processed by the Coast Guard The permanent Certificate of Number to be issued will be an embossed plastic card It will show the number to be affixed to each side"
  ],
